        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="card1 card text-start">
       
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Search Filter</h4>
            <p class="card-text">Utilize a search filter within the user's repository list to quickly locate repositories by name. This feature enhances navigation and efficiency.</p>
        </div>
       </div>

        <div class="card text-start card1 ">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="card-title">Commit History Visualization</h4>
                <p class="card-text">Visualize commit activity over the past year with an interactive graph. Simply click on a repository row to view the commit history, providing insights into the repository's development.</p>
            </div>
       </div>
       <div class="card text-start card1 ">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="card-title">Contributors List</h4>
                <p class="card-text">Explore the list of contributors for each repository along with their contribution counts. Recognize and appreciate the collaborative efforts behind each project.</p>
            </div>
       </div>
       <div class="card text-start card1 ">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="card-title">Repository Detail View</h4>
                <p class="card-text">Dive deeper into each repository with a detailed view that includes the README file, a list of recent commits, and open issues. Access this detailed view by clicking the "View" button on the User Repository Table.</p>
            </div>
       </div>
       <div class="card text-start card1 ">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4 class="card-title">Rate Limit Handling</h4>
                <p class="card-text">Experience seamless browsing with our rate limit handling feature. We gracefully manage GitHub's API rate limits by caching data and informing users, ensuring uninterrupted access and up-to-date information.</p>
            </div>
